{
  "assistant": {
    "version": "2",
    "provider": {
      "name": "acp",
      "servers": [
        {
          "name": "andy-acp-example",
          "command": "dotnet",
          "args": [
            "run",
            "--project",
            "/absolute/path/to/andy-acp/examples/Andy.Acp.Examples",
            "--",
            "--server"
          ],
          "env": {},
          "description": "Andy ACP Example Server - demonstrates ACP protocol implementation"
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  "// Note": [
    "This is an example Zed configuration for the Andy ACP server.",
    "Copy the 'assistant' section to your Zed settings.json file.",
    "",
    "Location of Zed settings.json:",
    "  - macOS/Linux: ~/.config/zed/settings.json",
    "  - Windows: %APPDATA%\\Zed\\settings.json",
    "",
    "IMPORTANT: Replace '/absolute/path/to/andy-acp' with the actual",
    "absolute path to your andy-acp repository directory.",
    "",
    "Alternative using published binary:",
    "1. Publish the example:",
    "   cd examples/Andy.Acp.Examples",
    "   dotnet publish -c Release -r osx-arm64 --self-contained -o ./bin/publish",
    "",
    "2. Update configuration:",
    "   \"command\": \"/absolute/path/to/andy-acp/examples/Andy.Acp.Examples/bin/publish/Andy.Acp.Examples\",",
    "   \"args\": [\"--server\"]",
    "",
    "Testing the connection:",
    "1. Open Zed Editor",
    "2. Open Assistant Panel: Cmd+? (macOS) or Ctrl+? (Windows/Linux)",
    "3. Check connection status",
    "4. Try using the assistant - it should connect to your ACP server",
    "",
    "Available tools in this example:",
    "  - ping: Simple health check",
    "  - echo: Echoes back input data",
    "  - test: Demonstrates parameter handling",
    "",
    "Debugging:",
    "- Check stderr output for server logs",
    "- Test manually: echo '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"ping\",\"id\":1}' | dotnet run -- --server",
    "- Verify all paths are absolute and correct",
    "- Ensure dotnet is in your PATH"
  ]
}
